main event: A rancher in Sheridan, Wyoming observed an unidentified flying object on 18 July 1953.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for approximately 30 to 40 seconds,The object was described as round and white,The object's movement was from northeast to southeast,The rancher reported that the object was extremely fast and made a loud roar and swishing sound,No photographs or physical evidence of the sighting were found.
